HEADWORD: Wedded
<hw>Wed"ded</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Joined in
wedlock; married.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let wealth, let honor, wait the <qex>wedded</qex> dame.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to wedlock, or marriage.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Wedded</xex> love.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wedder</ent>⟦br⟧
